    <id><![CDATA[OTS_SA_R3_D030]]></id>
	<title><![CDATA[<Introtext style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; color:#cc0033; margin:10px -5px 10px 5px; width:738px; padding:5px 0 5px 5px; background:#e8e8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #333; display:block;">Measuring Results</Introtext>]]></title>
	<title2><![CDATA[Measuring Results]]></title2>
	<instructions><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:bold; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px">You want to ask Dr. Gomez a question about the row of the Value Map called, “Why.” Which metric below should you have prepared to ask about to tie in with the cardiology department’s priorities?</welcomeText >]]></instructions>
	<choices>
		<choice>
			<id><![CDATA[1]]></id>
			<isCorrect><![CDATA[YES]]></isCorrect>
			<choiceText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><b>A</b>. Patient Satisfaction</welcomeText>]]></choiceText>
			<KPIs totalScore="30">
				<KPI marks="10"><![CDATA[Customer Results Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="10"><![CDATA[Sales Progress Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="10"><![CDATA[Trusted Advisor Relationship Score]]></KPI>
			</KPIs>
			<branchTo><![CDATA[OTS_SA_R3_D030_A010]]></branchTo>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<id><![CDATA[2]]></id>
			<isCorrect><![CDATA[NO]]></isCorrect>
			<choiceText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><b>B</b>. Patient volume</welcomeText>]]></choiceText>
			<KPIs totalScore="0">
				<KPI marks="0"><![CDATA[Customer Results Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="0"><![CDATA[Sales Progress Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="0"><![CDATA[Trusted Advisor Relationship Score]]></KPI>
			</KPIs>
			<branchTo><![CDATA[OTS_SA_R3_D030_B010]]></branchTo>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<id><![CDATA[3]]></id>
			<isCorrect><![CDATA[NO]]></isCorrect>
			<choiceText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><b>C</b>. Resource utilization</span></welcomeText>]]></choiceText>
			<KPIs totalScore="15">
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Customer Results Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Sales Progress Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Trusted Advisor Relationship Score]]></KPI>
			</KPIs>
			<branchTo><![CDATA[OTS_SA_R3_D030_B010]]></branchTo>
		</choice>
		
		<choice>
			<id><![CDATA[4]]></id>
			<isCorrect><![CDATA[NO]]></isCorrect>
			<choiceText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><b>D</b>. Requirement for consults</span></welcomeText>]]></choiceText>
			<KPIs totalScore="0">
				<KPI marks="0"><![CDATA[Customer Results Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="0"><![CDATA[Sales Progress Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="0"><![CDATA[Trusted Advisor Relationship Score]]></KPI>
			</KPIs>
			<branchTo><![CDATA[OTS_SA_R3_D030_B010]]></branchTo>
		</choice>
		
	</choices>
	<summary><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px">Although Dr. Gomez has expressed to you that she is focused on achieving patient treatment goals, it doesn’t necessarily follow that patient volume (Choice B) would be the best metric she would use to measure the progress toward that priority. In fact, an increase in patient volume would more likely be a result of achieving patient treatment goals.  The department might be concerned with measuring resource utilization (Choice C) or requirement for consults (Choice D), but those metrics are not as closely linked to the priorities you just confirmed with Dr. Gomez. Patient satisfaction is the metric which ties in closest to the cardiology department’s priorities of achieving patient treatment goals and maintaining/improving their professional reputation. Choice A is the best answer.</welcomeText>]]></summary>
